# iroh-ffi native/generated artifacts are NOT committed — they are large
# third-party binaries. Only our hand-written adapters and the gradle/podspec
# config are tracked. How they are reconstructed (git-ignored):
#   iOS      — the podspec's prepare_command downloads the official release
#              xcframework + IrohLib.swift (see ios/CentraidTunnel.podspec).
#   Android  — gradle resolves the official `computer.iroh:iroh-android` AAR
#              from Maven Central (natives for all four ABIs; no local step).

# iOS: the official release xcframework + the uniffi-generated Swift wrapper,
# plus the version marker the prepare_command uses to refetch on a tag bump.
ios/Iroh.xcframework/
ios/IrohLib.swift
ios/.iroh-version

# Android: OBSOLETE pre-AAR vendored tree (cargo-ndk .so + uniffi Kotlin).
# Kept ignored so stale dev checkouts don't accidentally commit it; the gradle
# build fails fast with a delete-me message if these dirs exist.
android/src/main/java/computer/iroh/
android/src/main/jniLibs/
android/build/
